Decrypto isn’t really a word game—it’s a shared reconstruction game.

One person has an internal representation.

They can’t transmit it directly.

So they emit clues that are:

* informative enough for teammates,
* compressed enough to be efficient,
* ambiguous enough that outsiders can’t reconstruct the mapping.

